All Matters Construction – Privacy Policy for Internal Application

Last Updated: 11/25/2025

This Privacy Policy describes how the internal software application (“Application”) developed and maintained by All Matters Construction (“Company”, “we”, “our”) collects, uses, stores, and protects information accessed through QuickBooks Online and other internal systems. This Application is for internal use only and is not provided to external users or customers.

1. Scope of This Policy

This Privacy Policy applies solely to the internal reporting Application used by authorized employees of All Matters Construction. It does not apply to the public website, customer systems, or any third-party products outside the Company’s internal environment.

2. Information We Access

The Application retrieves read-only data from QuickBooks Online and internal systems for reporting and dashboard creation. The categories of data accessed may include:

2.1 Financial and Operational Data

Invoices

Bills

Expenses

Payments made

Estimates

Job and project details

2.2 Customer Data

Customer names

Contact information (address, email, phone)

Job-related customer information

2.3 Data We Do NOT Access

The Application does not access:

Employee data

Payroll information

Sensitive financial data such as bank account numbers

Tax filing data

Social Security numbers

Vendor bank information

3. How We Use the Information

The Application uses retrieved data exclusively for internal operational purposes, including:

Dashboard reporting

Job performance analysis

Financial overview and trend monitoring

Business decision support

Power BI internal reporting

Data is never used for marketing, sales, or advertising.

4. Data Storage and Retention
4.1 Storage Location

Data is stored in a local encrypted database on an internal Windows system within the Company’s network.

No cloud storage is used.

4.2 Retention

Financial and project data may be stored indefinitely for reporting and historical analysis.

Only the most recent retrieval logs (success/failure messages) are stored; logs do not contain sensitive financial details.

5. Data Sharing

The Company does not share data retrieved by the Application with:

External third parties

Vendors or contractors

External analytics or marketing companies

Intuit outside the standard API flow

The ONLY internal system that consumes this data is Power BI, running entirely inside the Company’s environment.

No data ever leaves internal infrastructure unless legally required.

6. Security Measures

All Matters Construction implements industry-standard security measures to protect Application data, including:

6.1 Technical Security

Encrypted local database

Secure OAuth 2.0 integration with QuickBooks

HTTPS/TLS for all API communication

Restricted access to the Application server

No public network exposure

6.2 Access Control

Access limited to Owners, Project Managers, the General Manager, and IT

Local authentication within the Application

Permissions mirror users' existing QuickBooks Online access levels

IT has exclusive access to stored OAuth tokens

6.3 Monitoring

Minimal logs are stored (success/error retrieval logs)

Logs do NOT contain personally sensitive data

Usage may be monitored for security and compliance

7. User Responsibilities

Authorized users must:

Maintain the confidentiality of their login credentials

Use the Application only for legitimate business purposes

Follow Company IT and security policies

Report any suspected security incidents to IT immediately

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy

The Company may update this Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes will be reflected with an updated “Last Updated” date. Continued use of the Application constitutes acceptance of any revised terms.

9. Contact Information

If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or need assistance, contact:

All Matters Construction – IT Department
Email: it@allmattersgc.com
